<span id="freeTextContainer9463859350763124678">Many of these are pretty grim and are a fun twist on the old fairy tales. A good read but maybe not her best. I think I&apos;ve read some of them in the distant past and possibly even this collection. The impetus to read this came from a list posted by author Kate Elliott, consensus seems to be it was a mixed bag. I think for a first Lee read, I would recommend <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/81129.The_Gorgon_and_Other_Beastly_Tales' title='The Gorgon and Other Beastly Tales by Tanith Lee' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Gorgon and Other Beastly Tales</a>.<br/><br/>There&apos;s one thing I hate about GoodReads: finding out that an author I like has passed on, which is the ca</span>
  <span id="freeText9463859350763124678" style="display:none">Many of these are pretty grim and are a fun twist on the old fairy tales. A good read but maybe not her best. I think I've read some of them in the distant past and possibly even this collection. The impetus to read this came from a list posted by author Kate Elliott, consensus seems to be it was a mixed bag. I think for a first Lee read, I would recommend <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/81129.The_Gorgon_and_Other_Beastly_Tales" title="The Gorgon and Other Beastly Tales by Tanith Lee" rel="nofollow noopener">The Gorgon and Other Beastly Tales</a>.<br /><br />There's one thing I hate about GoodReads: finding out that an author I like has passed on, which is the case with Tanith Lee. I'm happier thinking they are working on their next book or restoring an old mansion or otherwise enjoying life.</span>
